x_n = \frac{\sqrt{n^2+2}}{2n},n \in \mathbb{N^*} \ldots
|{x_n - \frac{1}{2}}| < \frac{1}{2n^2}
\sqrt{1+\gamma} < 1 + \frac{\gamma}{2}
 \forall \gamma \in \mathbb{R^{*}_{+}}
\left|{\frac{\sqrt{n^2+2}}{2n} - \frac{1}{2}}\right| = {\frac{\sqrt{n^2+2}}{2n} - \frac{1}{2}}
{\frac{\sqrt{n^2+2}}{2n} - \frac{1}{2}}>0
\frac{\sqrt{n^2+2}}{2n}>\frac{1}{2} \Rightarrow \frac{n^2+2}{n^2}>1 \Rightarrow 1+\frac{2}{n^2}>1
\frac{\sqrt{n^2+2}}{2n} - \frac{1}{2}=\frac{\sqrt{\frac{2}{n^2}+1}}{2} - \frac{1}{2}
\sqrt{1+\gamma} < 1 + \frac{\gamma}{2}
\frac{\sqrt{\frac{2}{n^2}+1}}{2} - \frac{1}{2}<\frac{\frac{1}{n^2}+1}{2} - \frac{1}{2}=\frac{1}{2n^2}
(\sqrt{n^2+2}-n)(\sqrt{n^2+2}+n)=2
\sqrt{n^2+2}+n>2n
0<\sqrt{n^2+2}-n<\frac 1{n}  
0<\frac{\sqrt{n^2+2}}{2n}-\frac12<\frac 1{2n^2} . 
